The paper deals with randomized methods for approximate singular value decomposition, which is a topic in numerical linear algebra (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the performance of these methods in data applications, such as principal component analysis (cs.LG, cs.CV). Additionally, the paper introduces a new randomized block Krylov method, which is related to classic algorithms in numerical linear algebra (cs.DS, cs.IT).
